narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would very much recommend this course. Professor Auld is fantastic, and he made the 9am course very worth it. I think this course could succeed as either a lecture or seminar. I feel that I am leaving this course with knowledge extended far beyond just resource management and Canada; however I feel very well-informed on that front as well.
Yes, if you are interested in Canada and its econ, poli aspects, take this course. I knew nothing about Canada, but walked away with a greater interest in the country.
Yes. The Canadian case studies offer an interesting counterpoint to the US, making the class very interesting.

A general overview of resource management in the Canadian context followed by case studies in: Oil & Gas, Fisheries, Water, Forestry and Mining. The issues discussed are unique to Canada but there is some integration of US-relevant themes.
